Somewhere on the west cost of the USA. Probably northern California
Zion National Park from the valley floor
Angel's Landing in Zion National Park. The hike to the viewpoint is pretty scary, following a narrow ridge of rock with sheer cliff faces on either side.
Horseshoe Bend near Page, Arizona. This was way bigger than I had imagined from seeing pictures before I was there.
Light and shadow in Lower Antelope Canyon, Arizona.
Route 163 through Monument Valley
View from the Green River Overlook at Island in the Sky in Canyonlands National Park. Up there with the most breathtaking viewpoints I've ever visited.
A track through a field in Oxfordshire.
Overlooking the River Cam in Cambridge, England
King's College Cambridge from the top of the tower of Great St Mary's Church.
The Wren Library of Trinity College Cambridge, taken from Neville's Court
The red arrows performing a display at the Bournemouth Air Show
The plough above Pavillion E (which houses the geometers) at the Department of Pure Mathematics and Mathematical Statistics in Cambridge.
A bee (which I think was dead, but therefore easy to get a picture of) on an allotment in Bochum, Germany.

A swan on the Ruhr River near Kemnader See in Germany. I didn't think much of the photo while I was taking it, but when I looked back the water was so still and dark against the white swan, and the reflection so clear that I heightened the effect with some adjustments in Lightroom.
Punts tied up on the River Cam behind Trinity College.
Seljalandsfoss in Iceland
Close-up of Seljalandsfoss in Iceland. The path takes you all the way around the back of the waterfall, which is pretty cool.
Don't ask me how you pronounce it, because I have no idea... It's a beautiful place though.
Long exposure shot with rear flash of an old playhouse in my parents' garden that I outlined with a sparkler.
I think the longest exposure shot I've ever done (almost 8 1/2 minutes) of the London Eye using a neutral density filter. Very happy with how it turned out.

Long exposure shot of Big Ben and passing traffic at night. It's always worth waiting for a bus to go past, they leave the best light trails.

At the moment, the tower has been hidden behind scaffolding for well over a year. I look forward to it being visible again.
A photographer photographing the sunset, silhouetted against the sky in Dorset, England
A close-up of Lady Liberty :)
Taken in the processing hall of Ellis Island immigration station. I love the tiled ceiling and the light fixtures.
The World Trade Center subway station in New York at Christmas
A New York intersection near Times Square
30 Rock with the iconic Christmas tree at its base. Unfortunately they turned the tree lights off about 2 minutes before I took this photo, but I still like it.
